pwd --> print working directory                     
ls  --> list the content of directory               |Relative Path - a file or directory relative to current directory |
cd  --> change directory                            |absolute path - file or directory location in relation the rootdir|
file--> obtain information about what type of file  
man <command> --> show command manual  page
mkdir --> making a directory
rmdir --> remove empty directory
touch --> create blank file
cp  --> copy file or directory
mv  --> move file or directory
rm  --> remove file
vi  --> edit a file
cat --> view a file 
less --> view a large file
chmod --> change permission on a file or directory  |r= read w= write e= execute                                 
head --> view the first n line of data
tail --> view the last n line of data
sort --> Organise the data into order
nl  --> print line number before data
wc  --> print a count of lines, word, and characters
cut --> cut data into fields and only display specified fields
sed --> do a search and replace on the data
uniq --> remove duplicate lines
tac --> print data in reverse order
egrep --> view lines of data which match a particular pattern       
 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|    '>'  --> save output to a file                                            |
|    '>>' --> append output to a file                                          |
|    '<'  --> read input from a file                                           |
|    '2>' --> redirect error messages                                          |
|    '|'  --> send output from one program as input to another program         |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------    
